26.2.4 Which Function Mode
--------------------------

Which Function mode is a global minor mode (*note Minor Modes::) which
displays the current function name in the mode line, updating it as you
move around in a buffer.

   To either enable or disable Which Function mode, use the command
`M-x which-function-mode'.  Which Function mode is a global minor mode.
By default, it takes effect in all major modes major modes that know
how to support it (i.e., all the major modes that support Imenu).  You
can restrict it to a specific list of major modes by changing the value
of the variable `which-func-modes' from `t' (which means to support all
available major modes) to a list of major mode names.


